HEADWORD: Silica
<hw>Sil"i*ca</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from L.
<ets>silex</ets>, <ets>silics</ets>, a flint.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Silicon dioxide, SiO<?/. It constitutes ordinary quartz (also opal
and tridymite), and is artificially prepared as a very fine, white,
tasteless, inodorous powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

